<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-244-398 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 750 001  OV: 09 749 973.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Jan 14 1991 v8 n2 p85(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft Corp.: Word for OS/2 1.10. (Software Review) (one offour evaluations of OS/2-based word processing software in 'PMbolsters OS/2 word processors.') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Milenbach, Julian.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Microsoft Corp's $495 Word for OS/2 1.1 word processor uses thePresentation Manager interface and shares the same graphical userinterface (GUI) as the DOS and Windows versions of the product.andO;The documentation is well organized, and the program has manypowerful features but is nevertheless easy to use.andP;  Style sheetsare saved as part of a document instead of in separate files, andthe outlining facility is excellent.andP;  Word for OS/2 1.1 includes aspelling checker, thesaurus, hyphenation dictionary and powerfulmacro facility that lets the user record complex sequences ofactions and commands.andP;  Users can edit up to nine documents inseparate window and can import and export files between a widevariety of formats.andP;  Word for OS/2 1.1 is the most powerful OS/2word processor currently available.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Word for OS/2 1.1 (Word processing software)(evaluation).andO;Topic:     Word Processing SoftwareEvaluationOS/2.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Vital signs. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Microsoft Corp.andM;WORD FOR OS/2 1.10andM;There is very little difference between Microsoft's Word for OS/2 and itsDOS-based Word 5.5 and Word for Windows.andP;  With Word for Windows and Word forOS/2 sporting virtually identical menu structures and screen layouts, thethree versions of this popular word processor offer a smooth migration pathacross environments.andM;Installation of the recently released Word for OS/2 was straightforward,although this PM program lacks a graphical windowed installation process withcheck boxes for making selections.andM;The Windows and OS/2 products are so alike that Word for OS/2's concise andwell-organized hard-copy documentation is the same as the Windows version ofthe product.andP;  The on-line help facility, which includes a key-word search,eases the process of learning Word.andP;  Unfortunately, the on-line tutorialcontained a bug that prevented the Word macros within the tutorial fromshowing the correct menu graphics.andM;According to Microsoft officials, this was due to an OS/2 1.3 StandardEdition bug that occurs when operating Presentation Manager applications (seestory above).andP;  Microsoft provided a corrective tutorial dynamic link libraryfile that solved the problem.andP;  Once working, the comprehensive on-linetutorial proved well worth the wait.andM;Word offers a host of features for organizing and formatting documents.andP;  Muchof the formatting can be accomplished using the on-screen ribbon and ruler,which provide icons for direct formatting of text.andM;Word also excels in its outlining facility, which can be used at any timewhile editing a document.andP;  Additional formatting support is implemented withdocument templates and style sheets.andP;  Templates, which can be defined andsaved, define the overall formatting of a Word document and can includeglossary entries, styles, macros and even boilerplate text.andM;The style sheet is part of the Word for OS/2 document itself rather thanbeing a separate file.andP;  Word for OS/2 also contains a facility for definingand manipulating textual tables within a document; and Presentation Managermetafiles as well as CGM and PCX graphics files from other programs can beincluded in Word documents.andM;Other utilities include a spelling checker, thesaurus and hyphenationdictionary.andP;  Word's powerful macro facility lets the user record sets ofactions and commands that can be invoked later through keystrokes or themacro pull-down menu.andP;  The Word for OS/2 menus can even be customized toinclude user-defined macros.andM;Word for OS/2 also includes DDE support, which worked when tested withMicrosoft Excel for OS/2.andM;Word allows as many as nine documents to be edited in separate windows, whichmay be viewed individually or in any combination.andP;  Files may be imported fromand exported to an assortment of formats including ASCII text, RTF, BIFF,Multiplan, other Word formats, WordPerfect, MultiMate and WordStar.andM;----------Microsoft Corp.andM;Redmond, Wash.andP;  (800) 426-9400andM;Publicly heldandM;Year established: 1975andM;Number of employees: 5,500andM;Gross annual revenue (1990): $1.18 billionandM;Net income (1990): $279.2 millionandM;Source: Information supplied by company.andM;</TEXT></DOC>